Hey @Luap99 & @kyounghunJang  great to see this merged!

I just checkout podman repository and `make binaries`, then running `podman info --format=json` I am getting 

```json
{
    "host": {
       ...,
       "networkBackendInfo": {
           "default_network": "podman"
       }
    },
    ...
}
```

Great! But the default_network is using `snake_case` when all other property in the json is using `camelCase`, is this expected?

> Hey [@Luap99](https://github.com/Luap99) & [@kyounghunJang](https://github.com/kyounghunJang) great to see this merged!
